Package net.sf.jclec.mo.command

Command package.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Command
    A generic command to perform an operation over a set of individuals.
    CrowdingDistanceCalculator
    A command to compute the crowding distance defined by NSGA-II.
    DasDennisVectorGenerator
    A command to generate a set of weight vectors using Das and Dennis' method.
    FeasibleCounter
    A command to count the number of feasible solutions within the given population.
    InfeasibleCounter
    A command to count the number of infeasible solutions within a given population.
    MaxObjectiveValue
    This command calculates the maximum value of an objective function within the population.
    MinObjectiveValue
    This command calculates the minimum value of an objective function within the population.
    NonDominatedFeasibleSolutionsExtractor
    This command extracts the non-dominated solutions of the given population considering that the population can contain both feasible and infeasible solutions.
    NonDominatedSolutionsExtractor
    This command extracts the non-dominated solutions of the given population.
    ObjectiveInverter
    This command inverts the objective values of the individuals within the population.
    ObjectiveScaler
    This command scales the objective values of the individuals within the population.
    ObjectiveScalerNoBounds
    This command scales the objective values of the individuals considering the current values within the population, i.e. the bounds for the objective functions are extracted from the population.
    PopulationShuffler
    A command to shuffle a set of solutions.
    PopulationSorter
    A command to sort a set of solutions according to a given comparison criterion.
    PopulationSplitter
    This command splits the population in subsets according to a comparison criterion.
    UniformVectorGenerator
    A command to generate a set of uniformly distributed reference vectors.
